
Features:
	- info.plist manipulation
		- Add/remove user-configured searches
	- Add via URL (auto-discovery)
		- Get URL of frontmost browser
	- Allow alternates via modifier?
		Suggestions from one engine, but hold modifier to search with alternate
	- Allow custom icon via CLI option
		Is that possible? Reasonable?
	- Move JSON parsing to parent class
		The format should always be more or less the same (OpenSearch), so each subclass only need provide the URL.
			Note: Yahoo! adds a couple of fields. Use `results[1]` to get the list of results.
	- Change `name` to `description` (or `long_name`/`display_name`) and `id_` to `name`?
	- Add separate module to allow dynamic creation of Script Filters (?)
	- Move `Suggest` and its subclasses to individual modules (?)
			- No need to import all subclasses in most cases

Architecture:
	- Default to no variant (i.e. '*' or error)
	- Make `Engine` dumber
	- Make `Variant` ABC
		- Very dumb class. Everything is static.
		- Suggest/search URLs must only contain `{query}` placeholder

Commands:

	Config:
		- Browse engines & variants in Alfred
			- Add user searches
		- Browse user searches
			- Remove user searches

Update:
	- Update info.plist
	- Clear and/or update caches

	Add:
		- Add new search to info.plist

Engines:
	Engines still to implement in v2
	- Handle single/default variants (e.g. Yandex)
	- Make `Variant` class/ABC
	- Find more OpenSearch suggestion compatible search engines

	API/Format:
		- Default to URLs still containing {query}
		- Add support for variant titles
			Case: "Google (Deutsch)" but "Amazon Deutschland"
			- Use explicit "title" in `vars`/ABC?
			- Add `title_scheme` to ABC & JSON?
		- UIDs/UUIDs
			Identify searches already saved by user
			Should work with auto-discovered, URL-based searches, too
			Would they work for UUIDs in info.plist?
			- Generate from canonical suggest URL (containing '{query}')


